\pard\fs56\li2100 Chapter 1\
A Visual Guide to the User Interface\

\fs16 \
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\

\pard\tx2620\tx3120\tx3620\fs28\li2100 A user interface is more than the way an application looks on-screen.  It's all the ways the application communicates with the user, and the user with the application.  Sounds such as beeps are part of the user interface, as is the speed with which the application reacts to a mouse click.  Still, the appearance of an application is a large part of its user interface.  This chapter concentrates on how things look; how things act is covered in detail elsewhere.\

\fs16 \
\

\fs28 The appearance of the NeXTstep user interface is influenced by the following goals:\

\fs16 \
\

\pard\tx2620\tx3120\tx3620\tx4120\fs28\fi-520\li2620 ·	A look and feel that's consistent across all applications\
·	A simple, elegant appearance that uses shading to give a 3-dimensional effect \
·	A color scheme based on black, white, and gray\
·	The mouse as the primary input device\

