\fs36 Buttons\

\fs16 \
\

\pard\tx2620\tx3120\tx3620\b0\fs28\li2100 Buttons are the primary controls for starting an action or setting a state.  Users manipulate buttons by moving the mouse so that the cursor is over the button on-screen, and then clickingÐpressing and releasing the mouse button.\

\fs16 \
\

\fs28 Buttons can be very basicÐwith just a word or picture on a rectangular, raised-looking buttonÐor they can be more complex.  The following figure shows some simple buttons that are typical of those used to start actions.\

